The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Rain relief for city
                                                                                                               Rain relief for city
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	The city was lashed by the seasons second Norwester on Monday evening, sending the mercury sliding by nearly five degrees and holding out hope for a cool poll day.        
	The powerful Norwester, with windspeeds of 50-60km per hour, hit Calcutta between 6.12pm and 6.15pm. The shower that followed lasted over an hour. Till 8.30pm, the city recorded rainfall of 21.8mm.        
	Over the next 24 hours, Calcutta and other parts of south Bengal could receive widespread rainfall, hail, thundershowers and Norwesters, said G.C. Debnath, the director of the Regional Meteorological Centre at Alipore.                                                                                                                                                                           
